SIMPLE: where
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Where
<hw>Where</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>pron. &
conj.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Whether</er>.]</ety> <def>Whether.</def>
<altsp>[Sometimes written <asp>whe'r</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men must enquire (this is mine assent),⟦br⟧
<qex>Wher</qex> she be wise or sober or dronkelewe.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Where</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Where
<hw>Where</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wher</ets>,
<ets>whar</ets>, AS. <ets>hw<?/r</ets>; akin to D. <ets>waar</ets>, OS.
<ets>hw<?/r</ets>, OHG. <ets>hw⟦amac⟧r</ets>, <ets>w⟦amac⟧r</ets>,
<ets>w⟦amac⟧</ets>, G. <ets>wo</ets>, Icel. and Sw. <ets>hvar</ets>,
Dan. <ets>hvor</ets>, Goth. <ets>hwar</ets>, and E. <ets>who</ets>; cf.
Skr. <ets>karhi</ets> when. ⟦root⟧182. See <er>Who</er>, and cf.
<er>There</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>At or in what place; hence, in what situation,
position, or circumstances; -- used interrogatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God called unto Adam, . . . <qex>Where</qex> art thou?</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. iii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ See the Note under <er>What</er>, <xex>pron</xex>.,
1.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At or in which place; at the place in which; hence,
in the case or instance in which; -- used relatively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She visited that place <qex>where</qex> first she was so
happy.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Where</qex> I thought the remnant of mine age⟦br⟧
Should have been cherished by her childlike duty.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Where</qex> one on his side fights, thousands will fly.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But <qex>where</qex> he rode one mile, the dwarf ran four.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To what or which place; hence, to what goal, result,
or issue; whither; -- used interrogatively and relatively; as,
<xex>where</xex> are you going?</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But <qex>where</qex> does this tend?</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lodged in sunny cleft,⟦br⟧
<qex>Where</qex> the gold breezes come not.</q>
<rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Where</xex> is often used pronominally with or
without a preposition, in elliptical sentences for a <xex>place in
which</xex>, <xex>the place in which</xex>, or <xex>what
place</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The star . . . stood over <qex>where</qex> the young child
was.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. ii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Son of man hath not <qex>where</qex> to lay his head.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. viii. 20.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within about twenty paces of <qex>where</qex> we were.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Where</qex> did the minstrels come from?</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Where</xex> is much used in composition with
preposition, and then is equivalent to a pronoun. Cf. <er>Whereat</er>,
<er>Whereby</er>, <er>Wherefore</er>, <er>Wherein</er>, etc.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Where away</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>in what
direction; <as>as, <ex>where away</ex> is the land?</as></cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Whither</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Where</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Where
<hw>Where</hw>, <pos>conj.</pos> <def>Whereas.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And flight and die is death destroying death;⟦br⟧
<qex>Where</qex> fearing dying pays death servile breath.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Where</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Where
<hw>Where</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Place; situation.</def> <mark>[Obs.
or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Finding the nymph asleep in secret <qex>where</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

